Test Mode: A test parameter has been introduced to activate test mode. When enabled, the program reads input files from input/test/, processes them, and writes the results to output/test_results/.

Test Execution: A dedicated test_run() function has been implemented to:

Execute the test cases using the test input files.

Generate corresponding outputs.

Automatically compare the actual results in test_results with the expected outputs in test to verify correctness.


This setup helps maintain accuracy and reliability across code changes by ensuring that results consistently match expected outcomes.